modules.description: Provides functions to safely coerce Obj.t values to specific types using Typerep for type representation. Works with Obj.t and Typerep.t to validate type compatibility during coercion. Used to safely extract values from untyped data structures, such as deserialized or dynamically generated objects, ensuring type safety during runtime conversions.

Provides type-safe conversion from `Obj.t` to OCaml values using type representations, with checks for compatibility and safety. Works with OCaml's `Obj.t` and Typerep types to validate and cast objects, ensuring they match expected types. Used to safely reconstruct values from serialized data or low-level object representations, such as in deserialization or reflection-based processing.
